<br>
One unique Saturday I had absolutely nothing to do, so I went there.  He was camped but I decided to log and just check the next day.  Sunday I logged on and did a camp check.  No response so I spent the next 3 hours and 1 CR later getting back there - I mistakenly went to the back of the FG castle, not the front hehe.<br>
<br>
Finally I get back there and he's already up.<br>
<br>
It was luck that I have my epic now, all because of an unexpected free day.<br>
<br>
While I don't feel sorry for those that don't have their pearl yet, I do wish some knew what it would mean for the guild if we had actively camped it during that time - no raids, no groups, no stopping what we were doing to go rez someone.  People forget about that part.<br>
<br>
Now, that said, we had no clue this change was coming therefore no reason to rush, but even I was surprised at the top 10 hadn't done their swap yet.<br>
<br>
All I can say, don't spend the time there.  Step in the zone, shout CC, if no one answers, go back and sit.  If someone answers, come back and CC again another day.  There's better things to do than fight over this!<br>
